description:
&lt;p&gt;Nuffield Health is Britain’s largest not-for-profit healthcare organisation. Join us as a Biomedical Scientist in our Cambridge Hospital and play your part in building a healthier nation.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Cambridge Hospital has a very busy oncology department which requires fast turnaround times and a dedicated service for day case chemotherapy and inpatients. Routine Haematology and Chemistry is analysed on site for all patients and clients including 3rd party and a busy private GP service.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Role&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As a Biomedical Scientist you will;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- Deliver quality pathology services and taking a share of covering on-call service out of hours.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- Perform biomedical diagnostic testing, interpretation and reporting, through to quality control.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- Keep records of specimens, results, reagents and consumables.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- Support the organisation in validating and assessing new equipment and developing new diagnostic procedures. This is part of our ongoing quest to deliver the very best experience possible for patients.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Person&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;To succeed as a Biomedical Scientist you will have;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- Relevant laboratory experience in multi-disciplinary biomedical science.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- Good working knowledge of different analytical equipment in a range of multi-disciplinary techniques.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- Great communication and team player skills.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- The ability to understand how vital it is to maintain good customer relationships and provide high levels of service in a modern pathology laboratory.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Benefits&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We want you to be the best you can be. We promise that we will support you with training opportunities, career development options and our unique health &amp; wellbeing focused benefits package. This includes free membership across all of our Fitness &amp; Wellbeing clubs, along with free private healthcare. Not only this but we also offer a range of lifestyle and financial wellbeing benefits.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Be your best and join us in building a healthier nation.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;Location - Cambridge Nuffield Health Hospital&lt;br /&gt;Weekly Hours - 37.5&lt;br /&gt;Contract Type - Permanent&lt;br /&gt;Salary - £27,500 -£35,750 per annum&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Applications will be considered as they are received and interviews will be arranged accordingly. We reserve the right to close adverts early, for example, where we have received an unprecedented high volume of applications. Therefore please apply early to ensure you are considered for the post. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
